      "message": "The password will not is included in the D-Bus.\nWhen phosphor-host-ipmid handle request \"Get Bootstrap account` it will do below steps:\n1. Create one user account such as openbmcRhi1.\n2. Call `ipmiUserSetUserName` to create the linux account\n3. Create random password.\n4. Set the password for above user use `ipmiUserSetUserPassword`\n5. Set call ipmiUserSetPrivilegeAccess to set the privilege\n6. Call `ipmiUserSetGroupAccess` (new API) to set user group.\n\nThe flow is the same phosphor-host-ipmid handles ipmi command to create the account. So it is secure.",
